THE RULES


The goal is to reach the opposite corner of the board with all your pieces.
If you don't know the rules you should select "Show possible moves".
You can move in each direction or jump over single pieces several times.


HOW TO USE

The colored numbers say how the computer judges the position.
To do a move click the piecce and then the end position

THE MENU


    Project
    
    
       New game: You are asked about the names of the player and a new game
                 starts. 
                  
                 Special names: If a player is named "Amiga" your computer 
                                will be that player.
                                In two player mode you can select the 
                                difficulty in the config menuor by adding a 
                                number from 1 to 5 to the name (e.g. Amiga2)
                                In three player mode the difficulty is always
                                one.
       
       Load / Save game: You have to enter the filename and the game is saved
                         and loaded respectively.
       
       Quit:      This ends the game.
                  I hope you do not use this item very often.
                  
    Config
      
       Difficulty: 
                  You can select the difficulty here. If you use difficulty 4
                  or 5 it is important to have a lot of patience or a fast 
                  turbo board.
       
       Show possible moves:
                  If this us selected you can see the possible moves if you
                  click at a piece.
                 
       Show moves clearly:
       
                  The color of that piece, which the computer moves, will 
                  change for a few seconds.
                  
                  
TOOLTYPES

      PWIDTH/PHEIGHT: sets the width and height of the pieces.
      RES:  sets the resolution. If you enter "RES=HIRES" a hires screen will
            be opened.                                               